Allow Quantity.sum (and other attributes  like mean  max  min  and std) to take arguments and pass them to the numpy function if applicable. That way  users get the full flexibility of the numpy API on those particular methods AND get the added benefit that the result has the correct units (and it all runs fast).

Add missing arg check. Implement "reshape" in Quantity that passes down to the underlying numpy array. This function would be used in instances where  for instance  a certain API would send a flattened array of coordinates or velocities with units attached  and you wanted to reshape the array into (natom  3) to be consistent with OpenMM's Context object.
